overview: "The user initiated a request to resolve a comprehensive list of
  issues within a pull request, ranging from critical security vulnerabilities
  to functional bugs and deployment failures on Vercel. The approach involved
  systematically addressing each problem: first, by securing the authentication
  mechanism with HMAC-signed sessions and implementing robust input validation
  for API routes. Next, several bugs related to PDF generation (NaN values,
  minute calculations, hardcoded user names) and form field behavior were fixed.
  A significant pivot occurred when Vercel deployments failed due to a Next.js
  security vulnerability, necessitating an upgrade to Next.js 16. This upgrade,
  in turn, introduced breaking changes in Prisma and ESLint configurations,
  which were subsequently resolved. Finally, persistent Vercel build failures
  were traced to the Prisma client attempting to connect during the build phase,
  leading to a lazy-loading implementation. The outcome was a fully functional
  and secure application with all Vercel deployments successfully passing."
